privacy.section2Text:
We may collect the following categories of data:
- First and last name;
- Contact phone number;
- Email address;
- Trip information: route, date, time, number of passengers;
- Messages sent through website forms.

privacy.section3Text:
Personal data is used for:
- handling requests and enquiries;
- organising and providing transport services;
- communicating with the client;
- internal administration.

privacy.section4Text:
Data processing is carried out on the basis of:
- performance of a contract or steps taken prior to entering into a contract;
- legitimate interests of the company: handling requests, managing services.

privacy.section7Text:
The user has the right to:
- access their data;
- request rectification of data;
- request erasure of data;
- restrict processing;
- object to processing.

cookie.section5Text:
On the first visit to the website, a cookie banner is displayed allowing the user to:
- accept all cookies;
- reject all non-essential cookies;
- customise cookie categories.
Cookies other than strictly necessary ones are not set until consent is obtained.

cookie.section6Text:
The user may at any time:
- change cookie settings via the website interface;
- delete cookies through browser settings;
- block cookies at the browser level.
Disabling cookies may affect website functionality.

cookie.section8Text:
The retention period depends on the cookie type:
- session cookies are deleted after closing the browser;
- persistent cookies are stored for a limited period or until deleted by the user.

terms.section3Text:
The website is intended for:
- providing information about LONDON ROUTE TRANSFERS transport services;
- receiving client enquiries;
- initial communication with users.
The website is not a platform for concluding automated contracts.

terms.section5Text:
The user undertakes to:
- use the website solely for lawful purposes;
- not take actions aimed at disrupting the website's operation;
- not use the website to transmit malicious code or gain unauthorised access;
- not attempt to gain access to the website's systems.

terms.section10Text:
The use of personal data is governed by:
- the Privacy Policy;
- the Cookie Policy.

transportTerms.section3Text:
The company provides:
- airport transfers;
- corporate transport;
- group transport;
- private hire and event services.
All services are provided on the basis of pre-agreed terms.

transportTerms.section4Text:
- A client request does not constitute a confirmed booking;
- A booking is considered confirmed only after all terms have been agreed;
- The company reserves the right to decline a request without giving a reason.

transportTerms.section5Text:
- Pricing is determined individually;
- Payment is made in accordance with the agreed terms;
- The company may request a prepayment.

transportTerms.section6Text:
- Cancellation or changes must be communicated in advance;
- In case of late cancellation, the company may retain part or all of the service cost;
- Cancellation terms may vary depending on the specific order.

transportTerms.section10Text:
The client is obliged to:
- provide accurate trip information;
- comply with behaviour rules;
- not cause damage to the vehicle.
In the event of damage, the client is liable for compensation.

transportTerms.section12Text:
The company reserves the right to refuse carriage if:
- the passenger's behaviour poses a threat;
- the passenger is in a condition that prevents safe transportation.

transportTerms.section14Text:
To the maximum extent permitted by law:
- The company is not liable for indirect losses;
- The company is not liable for delays caused by traffic conditions, weather or the actions of third parties.
